yingyinNormal.en: From lowly Neanderthal and CroMagnon, to early warriors, medieval knights. All leading up to lunkhead basketball man.
yingyinNormal.zh: 从尼安德鲁与克罗马侬人，到古代的战士与中世纪的骑士，所有都进化成了篮球呆瓜。

yingyinNormal.en: Baseball thinking is medieval. They are asking all the wrong questions.
yingyinNormal.zh: 人们对棒球的想法很低级，他们连自己想要什么都不知道。

yingyinNormal.en: Last year is that why you sent us to that Medieval Times restaurant? Yeah.
yingyinNormal.zh: 去年你就送我们去那间中古世纪餐厅？是啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Renaissance fair? More of a medieval, slash, age of enlightenment, slash, any-excuse-to-wear-a-codpiece fair.
yingyinNormal.zh: 文艺复兴集会吗？更像是中世纪，兼启蒙时代，兼找借口穿遮阴布的集会。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah. He does it every year. That's why he's sending you to the play. That's why he sent us to that medieval restaurant and to that button factory.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他每年都那样做的，这就是为什么他要请我们去看舞台剧。这就是为什么他请我们去中古世纪餐厅，还有纽扣工厂。

yingyinNormal.en: Growing into one of the great medieval trading cities, she truly came of age in the 11th century, when William the Conqueror built the Tower of London, which was to become one of England's grimmest prisons.
yingyinNormal.zh: 此后，伦敦发展为中世纪一个庞大的贸易中心，而到了 11 世纪开始繁荣起来，当时威廉一世兴建的伦敦塔，是英格兰其中一所最为森严的监狱。
